libsrs2
------------------------------------------
libsrs2 is the next generation SRS library from the original designer of SRS.
It implements the Sender Rewriting Scheme, a part of the SPF/SRS protocol pair.
Libsrs2 has been written from an entirely clean codebase with compliance, speed
and versatility in mind. It is platform independent and has no external
dependencies. It is thread-safe and heap-safe, and is suitable for large scale
applications and embedded systems and can operate without many standard system
facilities.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  libsrs2-devel-1.0.18-1bl4
  libsrs2_0-1.0.18-1bl4
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-6
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://www.libsrs2.org/

Canonical download:
  https://www.libsrs2.org/srs/libsrs2-1.0.18.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libsrs2-1.0.18-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libsrs2-1.0.18-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libsrs2-1.0.18-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsrs2-1.0.18-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsrs2_0-1.0.18-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsrs2-devel-1.0.18-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libsrs2)
  /usr/bin/srs2.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libsrs2.README
  /usr/share/doc/libsrs2/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libsrs2/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libsrs2/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/libsrs2/README

(libsrs2_0)
  /usr/bin/cygsrs2-0.dll

(libsrs2-devel)
  /usr/include/srs2.h
  /usr/lib/libsrs2.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libsrs2.pc

------------------

